This project provides Java API for Android that is much more
intuitively understandable than the low-level OpenGL API.

To be concrete, for example, creating a shader and compiling
it with the Java API provided by this project looks like the
following:

    Shader shader = new VertexShader("......").compile();

If you like this style than the code below with the low-level
OpenGL API, try to use the outcome of this project.

    int shaderId = GLES20.glCreateShader(GLES20.GL_VERTEX_SHADER);
    GLES20.glShaderSource(shaderId, "......");
    GLES20.glCompileShader(shaderId);

This project assumes OpenGL ES 2.0, so the minimum Android API
level is 8 (Android 2.2).


